qas.question: Where did early Iranian people establish societies?

answers.text: southeastern Europe, the Iranian plateau, and Central Asia

qas.question: What language came sometime after the breakup of Proto-Iranian?
What language broke up after the second millennium BCE?

plausible_answers.text: as the various Iranian tribes migrated and settled in vast areas of southeastern Europe
